**making mixes to create music instead of relying on APIs**
-> A local python-based mix builder

--------------procedure-----------------
Step 1. pip3 install pydub librosa soundfile numpy
    ydub → loading, trimming, mixing, exporting audio
    librosa → reading tempo/key, optional analysis
    soundfile → writing WAVs
    numpy → math for normalization or gain
Step 2. sound organization
project_root/
 ├─ stems/
 │   ├─ guitar.wav
 │   ├─ percussion.wav
 │   ├─ bass.wav
 │   └─ pad.wav
 └─ mix_builder.py
 Step 3. create mix_builer.py file